  "prompt": "What is the best kind of frosting for lemon cake?",
  "response": "The best kind of frosting for lemon cake typically complements the tangy and citrusy flavors of the cake. Some popular options include:\n\n1. **Lemon Buttercream**: This classic frosting combines butter, powdered sugar, lemon juice, and lemon zest, giving a creamy texture with a bright lemon flavor that pairs beautifully with lemon cake.\n\n2. **Cream Cheese Frosting**: The tangy taste of cream cheese frosting works well with the lemon flavor. It can be made with cream cheese, butter, powdered sugar, and a bit of lemon juice for added lemony goodness.\n\n3. **Lemon glaze**: A simple lemon glaze made from powdered sugar and lemon juice can add a sweet and tart topping without being overly rich. It also allows the cake flavors to shine through.\n\n4. **Lavender Buttercream**: For a more adventurous pairing, lavender buttercream can provide a floral contrast to the lemon cake. The floral notes complement the citrus, creating a sophisticated flavor profile.\n\nUltimately, the best frosting depends on personal preference and the specific flavor profile you are aiming for in your dessert.",
